title: Leaky!
text: Got this for my cats, put it together as per the instructions and filled it up with water and it promptly leaked all over the place even before the red indicator showed that it was full.  I figured I must have done something wrong, so I took it apart again, reread the instructions, and put it back together.  Filled it up and still leaked everywhere!  It wasn't even full.  I put a towel under it and filled it til it was full but obviously, that didn't help either.  I kept trying for a few days and it just kept leaking, so I finally returned it to the seller (Smarthome).  I requested that the seller refund shipping charges (at least the return charges) since they sold me a faulty product, but they refused.  I wound up paying about the same for shipping as the product originally cost.  I am appalled at this company for 1- selling a product that was clearly broken and 2- not taking responsibility for said product's faultiness by paying for shipping.  I would understand if the reason for the return was that I didn't like it or my cats didn't like it, which would not be the company's fault, but this clearly was.  I don't know if I got a lemon or what because it doesn't seem like other people are having this problem with the product, but mine didn't work from day one.  For what it's worth, I left it on while it was partially full and my cats didn't like it.  They may have come around if I hadn't gotten tired of cleaning up leaked water.  It might be worth a try if you can buy it locally and return it easily if needed.

title: Am very impressed
text: This collar really works at great distances. After using the shock feature a couple times (reinforced with voice commands) all I need is the vibrate or beep audio tone to call my dog in. One day on a friends ranch, as I watched I let my Border Collie wander on her huge and many acre horse pasture. It was windy day and my dog was enjoying the attempt of rounding up a flock of birds. When the amusement was over for us both and time to bring her in I whistled and believed that because of the wind and the great distance, perhaps 400-500 yards, she didn't respond and believe she could not hear me. I 'paged' her with a simple beep and she picked her head up and saw me waving and came right back happily. It has been a good back up to voice commands and training tool and perhaps a life saver. I do not use it every day but only when the situation calls for it such as a walk in the woods which try I do often as I live in deep country. The collar and device are very well made and have taken a lot of abuse. I am a little more cautious with the remote I keep it on a leather rope/string so it is easy to get to hanging from my neck.

title: Lifesaver for Kitten
text:
I live waaaaay out in the boonies, and it isn't unusual for me to find abandoned baby animals. I keep these kits on hand for those just-in-case times when I can't get the animal to a vet for a day or two. I last used this kit when I found a tiny, emaciated, nearly dead kitten. It was a Saturday evening, and I didn't want to bring my vet to her office for an emergency visit...I honestly didn't think the kitten was going to live. I used the Benebac tube and KMR (both included in the kit) right away, and the little guy made it until Monday morning. The vet recommended continuing KMR and Benebac powder (purchased separately - see note below) as directed until the kitten was strong enough for worming, vaccinations, etc. Here's a warning about the bottle, however. The method recommended on the package for creating a hole at the tip of the nipple is ineffective. The nipple is too large for very young or small animals, so they have to lick the nipple rather than actually suck it. Use small scissors to cut the top of the nipple off. The liquid will not come out too quickly once the nipple has been twisted back onto the bottle. You will have to squeeze gently, and be very patient. As the instructions on the package warn, never hold an animal like a baby (on its back) when feeding it from a bottle. Good luck!

NOTE: See my review of BeneBac powder. It's invaluable for anyone with critters on long-term antibiotic therapy.

title: Easy to use, works for most pet smells
text:
Note: I'm not sure what product it says I am reviewing, but it's the powder. So if it says urine destroyer, that's wrong, I did not receive that product.

I have a cat that throws up whenever she eats grass outside. We discourage this behavior but she sneaks out on occasion. Meanwhile, we have a young dog that sometimes uses one of our area rugs as a toilet and I've been using odor reducing spray to clean it up but it doesn't work well. So I used this powder after the last couple accidents and it works well. It works best if you can leave it on the carpet for a while, overnight is what I try to do. Then you vacuum it up and pretty much most of the smell goes away. The packaging says to wait 3-5 minutes but when I tried that, it didn't work well so I just let it sit a while so the powder can do its thing.

Overall, a good product. A bit messy, but not too bad. It leaves behind a refreshing citrus smell that hides what little odor may remain after you vacuum up the powdery stuff. I received two 20 ounce containers of this powder which should last me a long time. I like this a lot better than the spray I was using. It smells better and seems to leave the carpet looking better since I'm not scrubbing the stain into the carpet but allowing the powder to absorb it.

title: ... the appearance and initial quality of the product look great, there appears to be a lapse in the ...
text: Although the appearance and initial quality of the product look great, there appears to be a lapse in the design of this product.  We bought this as a cushion for a newer dog we just adopted and it was placed in the bottom of his cage.  Although we were told he was kennel trained, it appears he is not as he has done his business on this mattress about 4-5 times.  Each time I had to take the mattress out and put it through the washing machine (front loader).  I noticed after the first time of washing it that the cover was not rubber backed cover on the top area towards the pet but did appear to be rubber backed on the side facing the floor.  This means that if a pet pees on the top of the mattress it will soak through to the foam padding.  The foam padding has now disintegrated all the way to having a giant hole in the center of the foam pad after the 4th to 5th wash.  I only owned this for a couple months and now it is outside the return/ refund period.  I think if this mattress had a cover on it that was waterproof it would have saved the mattress as it would not have to have been washed so much.

title: Absorbs waste well; noticeable, lightweight clumps; easy to remove from rest of un-used litter
text:
There are some things I like and some things that I am not as fond of in regards to this product - Purina Tidy Cats Light Weight, Low Dust, Clumping Cat Litter, (Glade Clean Blossoms).

What I like:

-- this litter clumps well, and is easy for me to remove, while leaving the rest of the litter in place.
-- pleasant aroma of Glade blossoms that helps make odor tolerable.
-- each time I took a cup's worth of litter from the box, and poured it into the litter pan, there was not too much dust kicking up, as compared to the cat litter I typically use.
-- lightweight litter means I only have to carry 17 lbs. instead of 35 lbs of similar litter.

What I am not fond of:
-- the top of the box is difficult to open with my fingers. So, I used a bread knife to fully open the top of the box. This wouldn't stop me from buying more of the product. But, I would have liked for the box to have a perforation so that I can just tear it open more easily.
-- our cat tracked litter throughout the area. But, to be fair, this also happens with other similar cat litter we buy.

What I am neutral about:
-- We've used this box for the past 16 days for our 1 cat. There's about 1/4 to 1/2 of the contents of the litter left. We typically buy the 40-lb or 42-lb litter packages, and in the same number of days, we usually go through about half the contents of those packages. And, the price we pay for those heavier boxes is less than the cost of this 17-lb package.

Overall, I like this type of cat litter because it does what I want it to do: it absorbs cat waste well, easy for me to use a spatula to remove the noticeable clumps. I then add more litter to take its place. And, the odor while using this product is tolerable, in similar vein to our typical cat litter brand.

title: Amazing litterbox IF maintained this way
text:
In the span of 2 years, I have tried 4 different litter boxes for my kitty. Apartment living is challenging for litterbox maintenance, especially with a kitty who digs so much. I read the reviews here and can see why some of the reviews were negative. However, I have found that HANDS DOWN, this is the best litter box for containing odor, reducing litter, trailing and dust, and is also aesthetically pleasing, stylish.

Here is my secret for success:

1. I use litter box liners, which I have shown in the picture. They fit inside this particular model and keep everything manageable. I scoop my box once every morning, then top off the litter with a little sprinkling a fresh litter.

2. I use sweet scoop, natural litter and scoop and flush it directly into my toilet! I only flush one urine or bowel movement at a time, so I do not clog the toilet. It breaks up very easily and flushes. No stinky litter genie to manage, cheaper, and less plastic in the landfill!!

3. I sweep the little teency bit of litter trail which is only right in front of the step after I scoop. Easy peasy.

4. A huge pro for me is that there is a charcoal filter included in the dome of this litter box. It’s really awesome especially for apartment living where we don’t have the luxury of hiding the litter box in a basement!

5. Once a week, I just pick up the entire litter liner bag and put it in the trash. The bottom of the litter box is spotless. no need to worry about the scooper missing spots due to the curved pan shape, as some have complained about. Some have also complained about urine leaking out the side or the top not staying on. I have had none of these problems and I am sure the plastic liner eliminates any risk of leakage.

So products I use in a nutshell to keep litter area obsessive-level clean:

- this litter box
-Petmate jumbo litterbox liners
- Swheat Scoop flushable cat litter
- plastic or nonstick scooper
- Catguru scoop caddy
-small handheld brush and dustpan

title: cat bed warmer from Amazon
text: This is an economic solution to geriatric cats need for heat.  Does not use much electricity, heats ageing joints and is small enough the cat can get away from in without leaving her bed when she is warm enough. We tell her just to wait and in a couple of minutes she is all curled up on the heating pad.  As she warms she stretches out and ends up with just her paws getting warm still. title: Alright launcher with some design flaws.
text:
I haven't had mine long enough to confirm or deny that the bands wear out quickly. I did get a second set of tubes just in case. The launcher does work well though and it's fun to play with all the dogs at the park and be able to shoot different sizes of balls. I was going to get a tennis ball gun, but found this for less money and it's more versatile in that it can handle balls bigger or smaller than a standard tennis ball. The main con of this is the ball holder at the bottom of the handle.

The product would honestly be better without that holder as when you pull the launcher back to fire a ball, it pulls the ball handle away from your wrist. When you release it, the holder snaps back and hits you on the bottom of the wrist and it's bare metal against bone most of the time. I've alleviated this by wrapping the holder in some felt tape to make a half inch cushion that hits the wrist instead, but it's still an annoying aspect of the launcher. I can't complain too hard, though, as I paid 8 bucks for this and 5 for an additional set of tubes. The guns I was looking at were 20+.

title: No interest at all, but it wouldn't have lasted had she been
text:
From all the positive reviews and the hype in the description, I thought this would be a great toy to occupy some of my girl’s time and keep her entertained while I am working. I took it out of the box and let her smell it. I rolled it around a bit to introduce her to the sounds. She initially cocked her head, but her curiosity rapidly reduced to complete disinterest. I tried to engage her in play with the ball, but she just bumped it around a few times and walked away. The ball has remained in the same location on the floor ever since (6 days now), so I will be sending back.
Obviously, since she won’t even try to play with it, I cannot provide any feedback on the actual durability or longevity or whether it is chew proof. HOWEVER, my dog chews on her large black Kong and is able to squeeze it flat. Given that I can easily depress this ball in many locations with just my thumbs, I have no doubt whatsoever that she would have destroyed this ball within a few hours. Probably better for both of us that she’s not the least bit interested in it. 😉

text:

As long as there is snow on the ground, they should wear well, but will likely not last long if your treading on cement.

The fleece boots are probablly some of the best boots I've found that don't bother our dog to wear and provide adequate protection while not constantly falling off. They get a little soggy in the rain though, but that doesn't affect their performance. Good value for price compared with more expensive options.

title: Sturdy, but definitely not cat-proof
text:
It's not a great cat feeder, but it works OK.
Pros: the wide base and freezer packs make it stable and possible to use with wet food; plastic is sturdy
Cons: the lid lightly clips into the base at the center, and comes off with enough prying from the edge; the timer is accurate to ~1 hour; one of the four timers doesn't work on ours; the spring which rotates the lid is sensitive to the lid sticking
To salvage ours, I drilled a hole through the center of the lid and close the feeder with a bolt and washers. The tightness is tricky to adjust so that the spring can still open the lid. I'm the only one is the household who can get these feeders to work.
In the future, I would try a different brand and read the reviews closely about whether feeders are cat-proof.

title: Awesome! Definitely buy the timer as well.
text: This light is awesome. Absolutely amazing. I had another LED bar on my 55 gallon that I liked a lot. I was disappointed when it died recently, after only a year of use, but whatcha gonna do, right? I decided to try out this Beamswork after doing some research. Now I'm glad my old light died! This light is so much brighter, it's not even a comparison. Having the reds and greens mixed in with the white really makes for a much more natural light. The lunar setting is surprisingly bright but deep blue. I also purchased the timer, which works amazingly well. A little advice: When you don't use the timer, the "regular" setting uses all leds, ie whites, reds, greens, and blue (actinic). It makes for a beautiful and bright light that brings out a lot of color from your fish and decorations. The light, however is a little cool and not quite as natural. Whether that's what you prefer is a matter of taste. When you use the timer, you set the regular separately from the lunar. In other words, if you set the timer to turn off the lunar when the regular comes on, you will have the very natural light from reds, greens, and whites, without the blue actinic. Personally, I set them to overlap for a couple of hours morning and evening so that I have multiple phases through the day rather than just night and day. It sort of gives the feeling of morning, day, evening, and night. Oh, and my plants are doing great. Keep control of your water parameters, because with this much light you can get a lot of algae bloom if you let your water quality drop. Algae is generally considered unsightly, but it's very good for your aquarium. Personally, I allow the algae to cultivate on the back of the tank. I get the benefits of the algae, and because it's cultivated on the back, that's mostly where it grows. I don't get much algae growing on the side nor front because it already has a foothold on the back. Sort of like the concept of an algae scrubber. Some people love the way it looks. Others don't like it. I like it and it's my tank, lol, so this is the way I do it. Hope all this helps.

title: Dogs are being eaten alive by fleas
text:
My dogs haven't had fleas since I adopted them 6 years ago. They had fleas from the shelter which I treated with Advantage and it worked. A few months ago a friend with a dog spent the weekend with me and sure enough, a couple of weeks later I started seeing fleas on my dogs. I bathed them, vacuumed really good, washed their bedding and treated them with generic brand flea drops. They still had fleas so I purchased this name brand Advantage II. Two months later, after 3 vials and continued vacuuming and spraying the house and yard, they still have fleas. I don't know if this is counterfeit, expired or what, but it doesn't kill fleas.
**Update-I spoke to Bayer customer service. They said the batch I bought was NOT counterfeit. They went through a whole bunch of reasons why the product isn't working. Obviously the company can't just come out and say their expensive product isn't any good. Bottom line, my dogs are covered in fleas.

title: Best dog bootie we've tried
text: I tried at least six different types of paw coverings for our rat terrier so that walking through salted slushy snow in the winter would be more comfortable for him. None of the others stayed on and they weren't waterproof. I saw these and tried them and have used them ever since. There is a bit of a learning curve to putting them on and off, but my dog was good about it and we have it down now. He wasn't fond of them the first few times he wore them, but now he is used to them and he runs and walks in the deep snow no problem. He will walk long distances in very cold weather and through salted slush as well. They are kind of slippy on ice though as they don't have any strong tread on the bottom. I also have to keep his nails trimmed up well with them too or the sharp tips will poke through the rubber and they will leak. Other than that these are the best bootie we've tried so far.

title: Great for dogs, do NOT recommend for cats. Great product.
text: I would not use this product on cats of any age as they are very sensitive to it. It is a great product for dogs and it will kill the fleas.  The main thing is to have a container big enough to fit you pet into so they can be covered in the solution. On our farm we purchased this by the gallon and made up a 55 gallon drum of dip and put our working dogs in the barrel then poured the solution over the rest of their bodies.  For extremely long haired dogs as working collies, they hair needs to be soaked.  Use caution around the ears face and eyes as the fleas run there.  Have someone help you and begin pouring the solution around their as soon as they’re in the dip.  A 5 gallon bucket works great for smaller dogs. Used correctly this product will prove its self and the mix will keep for a couple weeks if you want to redip your dogs to further protect them from fleas and ticks.  Great product. Recommend wearing plastic gloves working with this product do not rinse out of your pets fur. Let dry naturally.

text:
4.5 stars rounded up to 5.

I bought a couple of these - they wash the stain our and do get the odor out, over time. You have to follow the instructions - clean, take cat from the environment while it dries, and then reintroduce cat once dry and smell is gone. Initially, after cleaning, the spots will smell like cat urine. I don't know how long it took for my pieces to dry out completely - maybe a week, or so. My cat soaked my large leather couch over a few days - I didn't notice, so it was just lingering in there, and a couple of upholstered chairs, in just about every spot: arms, back, seat. Times 2 - two chairs. UGH! I sprayed the seats and couch, and secluded my cat in the master bedroom for a long time. In the meanwhile these dried and dried and with that the pee smell of the cat, and the 'pee like' smell of the actual product went away. This really does work!

However, it will not work on getting rid of pee stains in my wool rug under the violet/UV light, and that is why I'm giving it 0.5 less star. The pee spots are from my dog - so I'm guessing this isn't universal.

title: Does Not Remove Strong Feces Odors
text: We are still testing this product to compare to Fresh Step Extreme litter.  My husband says the Extreme is the best on the market, but I dislike the Extreme because it produces a lot of dust. There is dust everywhere on the hooded litter boxes and around the floor. Also, it gets tracked everywhere and we have a huge mat under the boxes.  So I read a lot of review about litter and we absolutely had to have odor control in our five cat household.  Two cats poop odor would peel paint from the walls.  So far, I rate the Scented Formula Excellent for clumping and low dust.  In three days, I have not seen any dust on boxes or floor.  It also is not dusty when being added to the box, which is very important.  Cat urine odor control is great but poop order is zero minus zero for our little stinky cats.  After they finish up and leave the box, I will sprinkle Clear the Air Odor Eliminator over the area, which works immediately to counter act the smell.  Since we have three litter boxes, we plan to place the Extreme in 2 boxes and use 1 for the Worlds Best scented multiple cat because this box is closest to the bathroom toilet.  Now that I know the Worlds Best is flushable, I  will start discarding it down the toilet.

title: It works like a skimmer is supposed to!
text:
[[VIDEOID:436067b3358a05a667eed0e98067b1d9]] Although I can't speak about CAD Lights as a company, as I have never dealt with customer service and such, I feel I need to post a review that will really help people with this product and with skimmers in general. I've been in this hobby for nearly 10 years and have even worked in the aquarium maintenance business a bit.

Something that a lot of people new to the hobby don't understand is how protein skimmers work, or are suppose to work. I've seen every small protein skimmer under the sun and have tried a handful of them. This is hands down the best one I've used! It actually works like a large skimmer you would find in a sump, but as a much smaller footprint.

Those that have been complaining about the water just "fizzing" and never skimming or there being "microbubbles in the tank" need to understand that this is what is called the break-in period, and it is normal with ALL SKIMMERS - even the big expensive ones. My PLS 50 Elite dumped a ton of bubbles into my tank for the first few days and sat there "fizzing" at the neck of the collection cup for nearly a week. Low and behold, a week later it started creating skimmate and the micro bubbles went away. Skimmers need to develop some "slime" in the chamber to
one: seal the cracks to prevent exiting bubbles and
two: give a surface that the foam can build and rise on.
Squeaky clean acrylic doesn't lend to this that well, which is why the water just sits there "fizzing" for a while. Not to mention any oils and such that may be on the unit from manufacturing need to be washed away first. (Running the skimmer in a 50/50 vinegar and hot water solution for a few hours first can help speed this process up a bit as well.)

Also, the skimmer is only going to work when you have broken down organics in your tank (AKA fish poop, uneaten food, etc...) So if you put a skimmer in your tank a week after you start the tank, it's probably not going to start skimming right away! THE TANK IS TOO CLEAN!
Also, you want to set your "fizzing" foam at the base of the skimmer, below the collection cup, so the foam head can develop and rise into the neck of the cup providing more of a dry skim. This way you don't keep filling your skimmer cup with clean water.

I gave this skimmer 5 stars because for the price point, it's the best thing I've come across. It fits perfectly in my JBJ rimless 30 overflow (had to remove one of the media baskets), it runs very quiet, it has a real needle wheel skimmer pump mounted discreetly underneath the chamber, is easy to use, and performs like a "REAL" skimmer. Adjusting the flow rate can be a little touchy, as others have mentioned, but it's not the end of the world. I also suggest playing with the height of the skimmer int he water for fine adjustments as well. Once you get it dialed in, this thing is a true skimmer workhorse. I obviously highly recommend this skimmer. :) I'll make sure to post updates in months to come.

title: Works, but not the greatest. Won't purchase again.
text: I've had this leash in operation for almost a week. My two biggest complaints are that if you lock the leash (like let's say your dog is doing his business and you don't want the leash pulling extra tight on him/her to give the feel of more freedom), then you do simply push forward on the button to lock. THAT works great. But when you unlock it, it retracts so hard and fast it startles and jerks my dog's head a little bit. I have a 10-month Husky-Whippet mix (around 40 pounds). I like the ability to control the retraction as you do with some other leashes. Secondly, my girl LOVES to go on occasional "rolling" sprees. When she does these, I have noticed the tape gets so twisted and when it retracts (at Indy 500 speeds), it rolls up with the twists. I know this because the last 4 times we've been out, I've come back inside and taken out the leash the full 16' and it has twists in it and then reel it back in (semi-controlled) to fix it. So, this will work for now and I'll use it until it dies, but I won't buy this brand again.

title: What a game changer! Cat no longer wakes us up.
text:
WOW....what a complete game changer! Our cat used to always wake us up in the EARLY morning for his breakfast. He would start with low "meows" to be heard(so that we would get out of bed to feed him)...then as we would attempt to continue sleeping, he would amp up his meowing to LOUD meows just so that one of us would get out of bed to feed him. It was annoying and it really cut into our sleeping time. So we finally purchased this automated feeder and wow what a complete game-changer it was for us! Our cat has never woken us up again to be fed his breakfast.
The automated feeder just slides open and his breakfast is automatically "served" and it's been so wonderful. Our cat is happy, we are happy and it's just a win-win situation! Can't say enough about this automated feeder. Anyone who has a cat who wakes them up in the morning to be fed needs this feeder. If this one ever breaks we are definitely buying another one because it's been fantastic! I highly recommend it. It has been worth every cent. Ahh, to sleep all the way through until the alarm goes off has been priceless!

title: Got rid of our dog's fleas!
text:
Our dog has never had fleas before (he's 3.5 years old), but we noticed he recently had them. So we bought this flea shampoo after a bit of research/reading reviews, and gave him a bath with it. This stuff really works! But make sure you follow the instructions. It says to let it the shampoo sit (for 5-7 minutes?) after you lather it onto them, and that's what we did. We had to do it twice in a row, but after that he was completely flea-free. We also used a flea comb to be super sure we got all of them.

The scent probably my biggest complaint - it's really strong. It's a citrus/orange scent. I felt really bad for my dog because I know citrus is one of the few scents he can't stand. Honestly if I'd realized that, I probably wouldn't have bought it. But luckily our dog didn't really seem to mind it. It didn't bother my husband too much either, so maybe I'm the weird one!

Either way, the fleas are gone!

title: Good product considering it needs to meet differing requirements for different locations.
text:
We use this pet door to provide access for our dog (and our cats as well) from our home-office to an outdoor 10'x20' fenced pen. The product is a good solution for an exterior wall installation, especially considering that it needs to meet differing wall thickness dimensional requirements for various installation locations. We put one of these in our previous house, and it went 6 years with no problems or replacement parts needed.

The instructions are pretty good, just have to be quite fussy about drilling the two thru-wall pilot holes exactly level and plumb so that the outside openings will align perfectly with the inside openings when done. There is also little information given about how to deal with different types of siding at the exterior, as the outer door frame needs to seal flat and solidly around the perimeter to remain water-tight. We have over-lapping wide-exposure cedar shakes, so I used the outside of the template to mark an outside line for the frame on the shakes, and over-cut the shakes slightly (and removed them) to allow for a small caulking joint between the frame (which installed hard against the flat wall sheathing) and the surrounding siding.

The doors seems to be quite weather-tight, and the double magnetic flaps and weatherstripping appear to seal quite well. There are still only two plastic flaps and some dead air between them, so insulation value is not super. Keep in mind that this door (like most other pet doors) can also admit some of natures creatures into your house as well, so you may want to use the latchable plastic door panel overnight.

title: My cat loves to love
text:
Tl;dr 10/10 buy these and follow directions.

My smallest cat absolutely love to love on me. Unfortunately that means a lot of kneading behaviors on my skin with ten tiny sharp claws. One would think that after 4 years of life she would calm down with the needy cuddles but no. She has just gotten more cuddly with age. Literally my only complaint was how her claws hurt. When I rolled over at night it was play time, attacking my feet.

Finally I decided to give claw caps a try for her. I had previously tried with my big boy, but over our 10 years together he has learned the safe places to knead. I didnt remember the claw cap experience fondly, so naturally I was leery of a cheap pack of caps. I remember years ago I paid about 20$ for a single pack of caps. Super concerned for a pack of 14 to be half that price!

I will say these have not disappointed thus far. I counted them all out and separated the colors the day I got them and I really did get 13 unique colors out of the 14 sets I was given. I got two shiny clear with pink glitter sets (not a complaint from me!). Also included are 7 sets of glue, and 7 easy applicators for the glue.

I tested one of the applicators with the first set i bought and decided it was easier to NOT use those. Either way her first set of caps lasted a week. I figured I got them on too soon to her shedding the nails to strengthen them. No problem. Just put her next set on tonight! Make sure to follow the directions and clip the nails first though. That will help keep them on longer.

The only thing I'm not a huge fan of is ny poor baby has to be burritoed in a blanket with one paw out at time for me to do this. But alas, we must all make sacrifices for the sweet sweet bliss of no midnight feet attacks and marred flesh for the kneading.

10/10 I do enjoy these. They have made snuggle session so much comfier for me! No longer will i refuse the cuddle puddles from my baby girl! Even if each set only lasts me 1 week, I give 0 cares and I will consistantly be getting these for her.

It has not changed her behavior in anyway, she is still as playful and loving as ever and I can not rest easy knowing she won't be able to destroy my poor flesh anymore!

title: My cats give it a 5-meows rating
text: Pleased to find this particular Purina product line on Amazon as it's not always available in my local stores nor as reasonably priced.  While I strive to feed my cats dry food that is grain-free, not every variety automatically appeals to or agrees with them.  Contrary to popular opinion, one size does not fit all when it comes to cat food.  They couldn't care less about nutritional value, only whether it tastes and smells good to them.  Bottom line, no matter how high the quality, it's a waste of effort if the cat won't eat it or it raises havoc with their digestive tract.  But I struck gold with this one and hope Purina doesn't change the current formula or flavor.  I gradually introduced it into my cats' familiar dry food a little at a time and finally swapped it out altogether.  I learned  the wisdom of that technique the hard way but now can report, no digestive upsets and LOTS of enthusiasm for this variety .

title: Quality product, tough cover, dog loves it
text:
I have a large lab, around 90 pounds and fairly tall for a lab. I previously had one of those cheapo-beds from Wal Mart, which he did like but the cover was cheap and difficult to take off.

So I decided to upgrade to a nicer dog bed and found this product. I was a bit skeptical if the price was worth it, but if the bed would last a little more than twice as long as the one I bought at Wal Mart then it would pay for itself.

The bed itself actually has two covers. The first cover is plastic and has two "sides". The "top" of the cover is a firmer plastic which acts as a moisture barrier, protecting the memory foam. The "bottom" of the cover is a breathable plastic which allows air flow.

The second cover is the denim cover shown in the picture. It seems to be of pretty good quality with a good zipper, and is washable.

One thing I really like about this bed is that it's actually pretty easy to put the cover on. You just "smoosh" the bed a bit into a "U" shape and slide the cover right on. The memory foam will expand itself back into shape and fill the cover nicely.

The bed is large enough for my dog and he seems to like it.

title: My cat Callista approves of this fountain :)
text: [[VIDEOID:80b62263422305bf78828a65f5d24172]] I had been looking for an automatic water bowl feeder and came across this fountain. My cat is pretty picky so I wasn't sure how she was going to react to the flowing water and noise but so far she's been doing great with it. This fountain even has a blue LED light that you can turn on and it lights up the spout where the water flows from. It wasn't hard to assemble and is easy to refill. To refill it I just use a cup and pour water into the top. This fountain comes with a charcoal filter and my cat Callista seems to really enjoy it. She loves batting at the free flowing  stream with her paw and drinking from it. It does make a water running type of noise as there is free flowing water but it's not to loud or disruptive. title: Game changer for my aging pup
text:
My 14.5 hound mix has been showing signs of cognitive decline for a couple of years now. The longer it was going on, the more heightened her anxiety became, to the point that every move we made in the house had to be thought through so as not to freak her out and send her scurrying.

My vet recommended Senilife (along w hemp of course), and I felt that I was seeing quite a positive difference! During covid, there was a 2 week period where I couldn't get replenishment. During the time that we were waiting for the new bottles to arrive, I was shocked at how much my pup regressed into her extremely-anxious tendencies, and you could see the confusion in her eyes. This more than anything showed me how much the Senile truly was helping give her such a better quality of life. My girl is around 45 lbs, and I originally gave her 3 capsules/day. I have upped that over time to 4 capsules/day.

For anyone whose dog is starting to lose their sharpness, I highly recommend Senilife.

title: My nails are nice again!
text:
I am so happy with this lotion, it really did wonders for my nails. They're awful and brittle and used to snap over tiny hits on shelves or something else pretty simple. You name it, it broke my nails. Using this lotion, I didn't have to worry. They would bend in a healthy way that didn't just snap them right off if I hit something.

I tried other lotions that strengthened them, but ultimately they still snapped right off on impacts, which was so frustrating. They were stronger, but the part they would snap off was right at the edge near the skin, after growing them out for weeks.

With this lotion, I've been able to grow my nails and have them last. They've only broken if I REALLY hit something too hard or at a bad angle, that type of thing. I would absolutely recommend *at least* trying this lotion! It's very nice to your hands, too.

title: Avoid
text: I find this to be a horrible product.  My LFS rec'd I buy two of these when my Fluval Marine and Reef 2.0 LEDs went out.  I thought the setup for the Fluvals was bad but this is even worse.  First, one of the LEDs didn't work right out of the box.  I had to call AI customer support.  Instead of sending my out a new LED, they wanted to send me out the WiFi part that was broke and have me fix it myself.  Great, just what I want from a brand new product.  Took 1wk for the part to arrive, meanwhile my 75G tank only has one LED which is nowhere bright enough.  When the part arrived no instructions, again great.  After some doing figured out how to fix the broken one and got it working.  Now supposedly with two lights one should be the parent  and the other a slave.  Using the iOS program I can only get it to detect them both separately as parents which means they won't share the same settings. Now AI has decided to sell this product with minimal instructions in the box and nothing taking you through the setup.  Go to there website and there are no instructions you can download.  They have a few setup videos which are mostly useless. For the iOS setup the version of the app shown in the video is not the current one and doesn't have the same options so the video tells you nothing.  Given the reputation of AI I would have expected much more.  I can't believe I actually like the Fluvals better given how much problems they gave me.  Also, these are way dimmer than two of the Fluvals and the out of the box color of the light not nearly as attractive.

Pitched as a squeaky toy for all sizes of dogs, in my case a German Shepherd, and it will stand up to that claim. I had concerns about size for a large dog but it perfect. Also had serious concerns that being a "cloth" based chew toy it was going to be shredded in a day. My Shepherd has history of making quick work of anything but the largest Kong toys. So far so good. It's getting some work as I can hear the squeaking yet no signs of ripping, tears or anything. I would call this a nice indoor toy as I cant imagine it would hold up well getting run through the mud, grass, and general wet outdoors without turning nasty. Indoors its holding its look and appeal. Give it a shot... Well constructed. Looks great and is different then the masses of balls, sticks, rawhides.

title: Great Product with a Better Price
text:
I have a 75 gallon freshwater. I was running a Fluval 406 by itself and I just did not have enough cleaning power. I tried getting a used filter for about $80 and had nothing but issues with it. I gave up and returned it. I used the refund to buy a new Polar 525 gph. I was hesitant because of the low price but do not regret it at all.
This filter is less than half the price I paid for the Fluval. It has a much better flow rate and also has the UV sterilizer for algae control. It primes faster than any filter I have ever owned. My aquarium looks so much better now I have both running though it is a little overkill now.
Here is what I dont like. The intake and outtake connections seem to be made for rimless tanks. I had some issues connecting them securely around the plast rim. I had to remove the little plate that screws securely to the edge and just depend on the screws to hold it. It is secure, but I may look for alternatives in the future.
The spray bar is great but sometimes the pressure is just good enough for it to sound like a flute/recorder being played. It goes away with some adjustments but it can happen.
Overall, I am extremely pleased. I probably will not spend Fluval money on a filter again if this one holds up.

title: Purchased this for my 90lb 1 year old intact male ...
text:
Purchased this for my 90lb 1 year old intact male Doberman. Goes everywhere with my fiance and I and left with a family member while we work since he was a puppy. We live in a condo community with close proximity to neighbors. When we leave, even for a short period of time, he begins to bark. It doesn't settle down but rather he becomes even more frantic and will continue to bark the whole time we're gone.

After reading reviews we picked this collar. It has been a life changer. I have it on the progressive setting so if he keeps barking the shock will gradually get stronger. Before we leave we make sure he's gone potty and had exercise. He gets a stuffed kong and we leave the tv on for him. Every time we've come home he has been sleeping on his place. Nothing was destroyed, no potty accidents, just a quiet dog and empty kong.

He hates the vacuum cleaner so I put this on him while I vacuumed to see how it works. He barked once and it didn't make any difference. When he went to do the second bark you could tell he felt the collar. He got the point after that. Definitely not to leave on your dog all the time as it is big but works when they cannot be monitored. Only con is I must charge it all the time practically.

text: When in the car, my big dogs are seat belted & sit on the floor of my van.  My new miniature poodle wouldn't be able to see anything if she was sitting on the floor so I ordered this carseat. title: Son's Salamander Saver
text:
When my son first asked for a critter cage to store his summer time pets I laughed and told him to use a cup - just the way we used to when we were kids. Of course, all that changed one Sunday afternoon.
Sunday dawned like any other. It was a beautiful Sunday in August, and we took our son to a park for a barbecue. He played in the grass, waded in the pond, and ran after newts, toads and salamanders - actually catching a few! After a great day at the park we loaded up into the car to go home - my son bringing the day's haul with him (set up in separate cups and bowls). When we arrived home two hours later we began the process of unloading the car, bathing the kids and starting bedtime. An hour or so after getting home my son looked at me with a slightly worried experession on his face and said "uh-oh". What is wrong my child, I innocently asked. 'I think I got them all, Mommy', was his sheepish reply. My heart started racing. 'Got WHAT all, o love of my life,' I beatifically replied. 'The salamanders. I think one or two might've crawled out of the cup'.
I bought the critter cage the very next day.

title: Great cage, nightmare to clean
text:
Pros
The size of this cage is awesome. It's huge & perfect for my two boys. I also love that it has two levels, both with actual floors rather than just small platforms you find with other cages.
It was relatively easy to put together. Having two people made it much easier. And it seems quite sturdy. Been using it a few months now & have zero issues with it's durability.

Cons
Cleaning this cage really it awful, and I clean their cages daily so it kind of sucks. Because it's so big it's difficult reaching the back without actually crawling into the cage. The doors are large enough for a person on the small size of average to be able to do this, but it's not a ton of fun. The floors also have a grid-like texture, which makes scrubbing stray poops off a nightmare.
The opening to get to the top level is small & must be accessed via the included tube. It's fine for now but I see it being a problem as my ferrets age. The tube doesn't stay in place on it's own so my boys are Constantly moving it into positions that make it difficult for them to use. I didn't bother with the second tube.

Overall though a decent cage. A few design changes & it really would be the absolute perfect ferret cage.

title: Who knew?
text: We adopted a great cat in need of a little training.  With the help of this magic potion, we have been able to train him to do just about anything.  Neville is a very strong, powerful cat, and we couldn't get him to sit still to have his nails clipped, so decided to sedate him -- but it seems that he'd had that sedative in another life, and he turned up his nose at anything that included his crushed pills.  Enter Inaba Churu; he loves the stuff, all flavors, and using it as a vehicle, we were able to dose him with no problem.  So now he comes when he's called, sits on command, will lie down, will stop whatever he's doing when asked, and back-up when he's in the way -- but if we're going to tell him he's a good boy, he expects a nice gob of this treat to go along with the praise.

title: Cats love it. It's filled with good crunchings and munchings.
text:
The AvoDerm Natural Grain Free Cat Food is a quality product that both of my cats are devouring as their always-available snack during the day and night.

Let's start with the shape - these products are small and flat and round, which is the perfect size for crunching and munching. This is especially important for my "senior" cat who has sensitive teeth...he can really get into these and doesn't have to bolt them like a dog in order to enjoy them. The younger cat seems to take great delight is crunching them as loud as she possibly can...in the middle of the night.

I haven't personally tasted the cat food in order to make a flavour assessment but if the behaviour of the cats is any indication, they LOVE the stuff. Sometimes they will poo-poo their noses at the moist cat food which should be a delicacy, and instead wander back to the bowls of the crunchy cat food. I take this to be a positive sign that they really dig it.

One thing I've noticed with the senior cat, is that his breath actually improves after having some of this food. His regular breath is pretty ridiculous since he's older and doesn't always do a good job cleaning his mouth after a meal. But after a few crunches and munches of this dry cat food, his breath is significantly improved. It seems to help clean off some of the buildup in his mouth - and that's always a good thing.

Overall I'm pleased with the product and will be ordering it again as soon as we run out. The cats love it, and I love that the cats love it. And you'll love that I love that the cats love it if you love this review.

Love.

title: Great for mild escape artists, for major escape see my comments.
text:
Love this cage! Great for dogs who chew and try to escape. Would not be good for true escape artist dogs with major anxiety.

I have 4 American Bullies ranging from mild to extreme worst case scenario and when it comes to cages, I have a few different styles. Of my dogs this holds all except my extreme worst case dog with major anxiety and escaping.

My favorite thing about this cage is the bottom has the thick bars for their feet vs the thin metal grates. This style is MUCH better for their feet and more reliable when it comes to long term use.

I am considering changing over all my cage styles to this one (minus the major escape artist).

I put my major case dog in this cage and she was able to break one of the bars off and bend a few others in a matter of a few hours. If you have a tough as nails dog with the same concerns as mine, don't get this cage. The only cage that has held my girl is the ProSelect Empire Dog Cage. title: AWESOME leash!
text:
I love riding my bike and I love my dog, so this thing has been great for both of us. I've had this for about 7 months and my dog LOVES it. He's a 50 lb. dog and it fits him perfectly. It attaches very easily to the bike, and the bar snaps on and off with no effort. The first time I hooked my dog up to it he was hesitant for about 10 seconds but then he got the idea very quickly. Now he happily freaks out whenever I pull it out of the drawer to take him on a run.

I took the advice of one of the reviewers below and bought a $10 harness that is far better than just attaching it to his collar, because with the harness the leash attaches above his shoulders and doesn't choke him at all. Highly recommend doing this than putting it on a collar.

The great thing about this leash is that my dog can run at full speed for minutes on end. He gets a great amount of exercise and there is no constant pulling on the leash like when I had to walk him. I can't imagine not having this now. The rope did fray after about 6 months because of the constant pulling (I use it almost daily), but it is easily replaceable. You can buy about 100 feet of thin rope at the hardware store for less than $10. You only need about 2-3 feet to replace it. Easy to just unscrew the top of the bar, remove the springs and replace the rope. Take note of how it is knotted at the bottom and connected to the hook.

Couple things to take note: my dog does like to dart after animals (we have a LOT of deer where we live), so you need to be on guard if your dog does the same thing. He will run to the side and it will pull the bike to the right, but he hasn't come close to yanking me down, just made me a little off-balance. Also, he will tend to stop suddenly if he wants a break or has to go potty. Usually we're not going too fast when he does this but it is something to take heed of.

All in all this thing is great and gives my dog way more exercise and fun than a standard walk. Well worth the money!

title: Happy customer!
text:
We didn’t purchase this collar set from Amazon, but from a private person. He was selling it on Facebook Marketplace and we then found out he is a local online dealer. We got a great deal on it as he said it was returned because the person who purchased it used it once simply returned it. He offered to test it for us (the kit includes a tester), which he did. We’ve had it for a week and are VERY happy with it!!

We were originally wanting a two collar set but when we came across the single collar, we couldn’t pass it up as we had just gotten a 6 month old puppy (Great Dane) who is very stubborn and needed one ASAP!

You can use the remote for two separate collars and after using it for a few day we contacted the seller again asking if we could purchase a second collar. He offered us a new or used and we just purchased the used collar. If it works as well as the one we already have.. we’ll be very happy buyers!

The second collar will be for our 2 year old Rottweiler. I don’t think we’ll have to use it much, as he’s a pretty good boy, but now that he has a brother to get into mischief with.. we wanted to have it just incase. He also has stated challenging me (mom) sometimes when dad isn’t home and I give him a command- which isn’t going to fly.

So far for our Great Dane, we’ve only used to longer prongs and the vibration setting on about 40. He does NOT like the vibration at all and quickly corrects his behavior. We of course tell him “no”, “come”, or whatever command before using the collar but he’s very stubborn. After just a few days of using the collar his behavior already started improving. We’ve only used the shock setting twice on 20 when he tried to chew up the collar and dads weight bench outside.

Overall we’re very happy! It’s the affordable, effective collar we were looking for.

title: excellent product, recommended
text: Use it like a dog "toilet".  My little dog doesn't care that I put the bagged gogo stick right under his behind and clean catch the solid waste. Don't judge, but I am one of the unfortunate people who have sensory issues, this is perfect for those challenges as I never have to feel the waste through the bag, or smell it too closely.  Once you catch the waste you can keep walking the dog while the waste "airs out" in the open bag at the end of the stick.  The bag comes off easily when ready so you can tie it.  For hands-free carrying when not in use, tie a nylon rope from the handle loosely down near the bag ring, sling it over your shoulder or across your back (like how a quiver is carried).  The other bonus is it keeps on from bending down so much, especially if you have knee problems.

title: Good, not great.
text:
The screws included are total crap. They fall out regularly. I am either getting bigger screws or putting a thread locker on them. My Boglen busts through it like the Koolaid Man and will have the door flap 7-10 feet out in the yard with screws blown out but the frame still in place. When you follow the instructions for height, it seems high but it is perfect for my two.

Also while you have the door off, take a tool and make sure your actual door screen holding rope in in nice and tight. I had my top rope fall out and had to redo. The door certainly puts strain on the top.

Keep in mind that the door is held on with tension, so if you don’t keep the screws tight, the flap will fall out.

title: Pet Safety & Visibility
text:
I liked this product. It's a nice safety device for your pet:
- Rechargeable LED (only in the color of choice)
- Strong/Sturdy collar
- Reflective thread for added visibility or if the LED wasn't charged
- Waterproof case (with plug installed)

There is one fixed leash loop position. Depending on how your pet likes the LED light placed, additional attachments points may be a good feature to have.

Bottom line, this collar helps keep your pet identified, day & night, on land or in the water.

title: Wonderful.
text:
Great change immediately. Our 50# Golden was abused as a puppy by truly evil puppy mill operators. They would throw a bag of food over the fence every few days and it was law of the jungle determining who ate and did not. Ten years later he was still gulping and choking his meals and had regurgitation problems, and occasional bloat symptoms. We had gone to multiple AM and PM meals to guard his health. This Slo-Bowl was featured at a dog show web site and we found it on Amazon and ordered it immediately. The first time we used it we distributed ALL his meal in the bowl, where it fell into the spiral groove and made him really spend a lot of time and effort to tongue the food up to eat. He was a bit puzzled that one night and gave me a quizzical look with his head tilted, but from then on he has eaten far slower and no longer belches, nor does he have that neck-stretching symptom of pre-regurgitation discomfort.

A great solution!

title: WOW impressed
text:
Since I have 3 dogs, I feel like I've tried a lot of different products for pet hair removal. So I have to say that I did not go into this experiment with very high hopes, but I more like, well it's only $8 so if doesn't work, and it's got to be better than lifting the vacuum up on the couch, which is the only thing that currently (only marginally) works, and since it's a pain, I rarely do it, and that's why I have a pet hair problem.

To be fair, I have a couch fabric (purchased before my latest dog, whose hair sticks to everything) that is not recommended for pet hair, as it's a woven fabric and the hair literally weaves itself into the fabric. The contrast between hair color and couch color are also not optimal.

So it arrived and even my daughter (who never cleans anything voluntarily) was having fun cleaning the couch and did a small area. When I had more time, I did the whole couch and got a HUGE pile of hair. I'll tell you, it's also a bit of an arm workout, in a good way. When my daughter came downstairs after I was finished, she commented twice how clean the couch looked, hence the impressed title of the review. A couple of days later, I did the couch again, not as much of an arm workout this time, but much less hair.

I will heartily recommended this product. The only improvement I would suggest would be a hole in the handle so it can hang with your cleaning products. I fashioned a hanger from some hair elastics and hung it by the couch so I can use it when I'm watching tv. The yellow blends with my end tables, so extra bonus!

title: Fun but not safe
text:
[[VIDEOID:a826d252a75de503b098366ce8bb3129]] My kitty definitely "played" with this toy, but it was more of a nuisance than actual play. She would bite the metal rod instead of the feathers.

But as funny as it was to watch her with the collar on, I can't, in good conscience, recommend this toy. First, the colar is NOT breakaway so if she or the toy get stuck on something, it may not come loose. Second, unless the collar is so tight it nearly chokes her, the feather will not stay in the air - it drags on the ground. So again see my first point.

It's a great idea in concept. However a velcro, or at least breakaway, collar would be needed to feel safe leaving this on my kitty as she plays. She's far too speedy and rambunctious to be chasing her around while she does it. I'd be better off with just the feather attachment.

We adopted a German Shepard Dog from a shelter and couldn't keep her off the sofa while we were gone from the room, until the Sofa Scram. We put this on the sofa and immediately she stayed off the sofa. We only had to set it off a couple of times and she was cured from laying on the sofa. title: Dog Door
text:
Pretty good product. Just what I wanted in a 50 dollar door. Everyone was right about the narrow clearance for the screws (just on the bottom edge) Be careful of that. My door was metal so the minimal clearance for screws didnt hurt anything. If your door is wood then be cautious with your cutting, thats all. Door functions well. I tightened up the magnets (clearance)per instructions and my door doesnt blow open. Its in a breezeway between the garage and house. Door is tall and skinny. My female Lab is 24 inches tall (withers) and 9 inches wide so this door was perfect for her build.
Only downside is no interior trim. I bought a sheetrock corner protector (plastic 3/4" angle) from WalMart (or any hardware center) and cut it to fit around the edge of the metal inside my door. Works great.

UPDATE 3 YEARS LATER......2-07-15....Door is just fine. After a couple of years the door hinge loosened up and the door droop'd a little and that hurt the fitment and the noise it makes. I took the ole belt sander and sanded the edges back to a perfect fit and its still working great. My 90 lb baby goes through it at full tilt sometimes with no issues.

title: A miracle in a box- awesome, and humane is the PetSafe Gentle Leader Deluxe Headcollar!!!
text:
I love my size medium PetSafe Gentle Leader Deluxe Headcollar, in the red Rolling Bones design. It's perfect for my service animal Alleigh. She weighs 79 lbs. and is 1/2 Aussie Shepherd, 1/2 Great Pyrenees so she has a medium sized, long snout. The gentle leader is a better alternative to walk your dog safely with. It is more humane for your dog to wear than a standard dog collar other than the hanging of the pet's I.D., license, and rabies tags from because a dog can SERIOUSLY injure their neck if they suddenly bolt, jerk or pull on the leash if they happen to see another dog, cat or animal and get excited or want to chase, fight etc., that other animal. Your pet also might get scared in some circumstances and try to shy/run away from a noise, car, if they are scared/attacked of/by another animal, or any other disturbance quickly pulling/jerking on the leash causing themselves injury as well. Not to mention sometimes tangling themselves in the lead in in the dog's excitement or skirmish- which unfortunately can trip or injure you too if the dog is out of control!!! That brings me to the most wonderful aspect of what the PetSafe Gentle Leader Deluxe Headcollar does for your dog! It allows for your dog to safely stay in control from literally the very first time your dog wears it- if you work with your dog and follow the directions provided and watch the DVD. It really is a "miracle in a box" as I call it, for dogs who are rambunctious leash walkers or have obedience issues while on a leash. I first should mention: it by no means is a "muzzle" and be forewarned some folks may question you as to "why is your dog wearing a muzzle", for the gentle leader fits over and is worn by your dog on it's nose and around it's head/neck and looks similar to a standard dog muzzling device. I am asked this question ALL the time. It's rather annoying, and some people even want to know if my dog is ill tempered. She is the furthest thing from that, but being a working service animal, and highly trained she must be in 100% control @ all times with her mind focused on her "job". You will most likely have to explain to some people why your own he/she is NOT wearing a muzzle but a gentle leader and educate them as to why it is the BEST thing your dog could be wearing or ANY dog for that matter and that regular collar users could potentially inflict pain or cause harm.injury to their dogs. The gentle lead keeps your dog safely and humanely in control by allowing you to lead your dog by the leash being attached to the side of the lead coming off of the dog's nose and NOT the dog's neck. The dog's nose is HIGHLY sensitive containing all of it's olfactory senses and a dog leads themselves around with their noses. They will generally protect their noses. Attaching the gentle lead to the dog's nose guarantees that a dog will stay in control because they will not jerk with the lead on their nose, it will not be comfortable for them if they do that, BUT it will not cause them any pain, and YOU will be leading them around safely without having to worry about the dog injuring their neck if the dog should see another animal, want to fight or chase them etc. I can guarantee with the first use AND your dog will be transformed into a well behaved dog on a leash. The gentle lead controls your dog by controlling your dog's senses humanely. He/she will not pull, drag or tug you anymore on a leash!!! I give the PetSafe Gentle Leader Deluxe Headcollar, size Medium, red Rolling Bones design, that came with a matching leash & instructional DVD (this is my second gentle leader I have had another for over 2 years- they are VERY durable) 5 out of 5 stars- I recommend everyone who wants a well behaved dog and a nice time walking them to buy the set today, it's worth every penny and your dog will be happy, healthy and 100% leash obedient from the very first use if you follow the directions provided and work with your dog.

*** WATCH THE DVD FIRST & FOLLOW THE DIRECTIONS PROVIDED! This is not a "just put it on your dog and away you go" product in some/most cases. You need to train your dog to get use to the leader and work w/ them!

title: Order from Target.
text:
I ordered one of these from amazon and one from Target. The same exact boxes. I’ll start with the good; it works. My cats like it, and took to them easily. They help minimize the litter mess.

The bad things about this particular order. It came with tape all over the litter box, which left sticky residue all over the top and side of the litter box. Which, I think goes without saying, isn’t preferable when cats and litter are involved. Secondly, it didn’t come with the scoop. Not a huge deal for me since I have scoops (and the scoops that come with these are rather small which I know due to ordering the same box from Target) but it specifically states that a scoop is included in the listing and on the label. So, it’s annoying paying for something and not receiving everything.
All in all, I’d suggest ordering from Target vs from this seller. It’s worth the extra dollar.

title: Beware - don't store in your house !!
text: I purchased these because the dogs love the piggy slivers and I thought I would try them. Huge mistake - the first thing I noticed was the foul odor that they emitted. I thought that because they were lamb and smoked maybe that was the way they were suppose to smell. title: Not the cat amusement park I was hoping for, but they do use it.
text:
Needed something for our kitten, because she was young & rambunctious, jumping all over our stuff, and causing havoc in the apartment. We have 2 cats, but only one of them play with it, but I think that's just the territorial nature of cats, not so much that the other one didn't like it. My cat is relatively small, and even she doesn't fit well in the 2nd & 3rd tier cubbies if you wanna call them that. Honestly, she mostly jumps to the top & lays on the highest pedestals. She'll often use those top round discs to jump onto higher bookshelves, because apparently my cat think she rules over all of us.

As for build quality, the cat tree tower stands up pretty well even to the vicious clawings of my cat. I really do like that she has something of her own that she can jump all over & scratch her claws on. If it weren't for that, I'm pretty sure my furniture would be her next best option. The instructions could've been better, but hey, it's not a model rocket, just a cat tower. All the pieces were there, and labeled well, so it made assembly fairly easy straight forward. The only thing I had difficulty with was the little ladder part at the bottom. I kinda had to bend the metal brackets a bit to get the angle of the ladder to sit right. Everything has to kinda line up well for the overall sturdiness to be sound. Besides that, everything else fit together pretty seamlessly. It's pretty sturdy on its own to be honest, even though there's a little loop on the side that you can use to secure the whole cat tree to the wall, or another piece of furniture. If you have a bigger cat, you might want to really consider using that, because they could possibly knock the whole thing over, jumping off the top discs onto something else.

For $60, I'm pretty happy with our purchase. I wouldn't expect your cat to play with it so much, but I'm pretty certain most cats would enjoy having something of their own that they can at least climb to the top of, and use to jump around. That seems to be what our cat enjoys doing the most. Carpet upholstery is actually better quality than I thought it would be. A bigger cat with longer claws could probably shred up some parts given enough time, but hey, I'd rather they scratch the hell out of this than our expensive furniture. For $60, this is definitely a solid buy. I really want to put some floating shelves up on the wall a little bit higher than the top of the cat tree, so she has something to jump onto, I think that would make this much more enjoyable for any cat. Would've given it 5 stars if the build quality was a little better. This is like the low-end IKEA version of a cat tree. Will definitely work, and not fall apart, or get torn up right away, but everything has a shelf life. There's definitely better quality cat trees out there if you wanna spend around the $100+ range. If your cat loves to jump around & do laps around your place at 2am, then they'll probably enjoy this cat tree.

title: Convenient way to feed my large dog! (Until it wasn't)
text:
Whelp....it's been almost 8 months and I think it's dead. New batteries and reprogramming don't seem to help. It beeps and nothing works. Bummer. Reducing to 3 stars..but maybe I should go to 2.

Edit: 5 weeks later - There's no indication that the battery is low, but the clock lost 11 minutes. Easily reset it and we're back on track. No other complaints! I maintain 4 stars because it's not perfect, but it works as intended. I fill the hopper about once a week.

Edit 2: Duracell batteries lasted just under 4 months.

Original review:
We've been using this for one week so far to feed my labrador retriever and it seems to be working well. By day 2, I found him sitting in front of the machine just before meal time, waiting for his food. He eats 1.5 cups of food twice per day. I've measured twice and it's a little over, but pretty close. The first time we used it, the loud noise scared my large dog, but once he discovered that it dispensed his food, he had no issues with the sound. It's now sitting on a folded towel on the tile floor and not nearly as loud. Although a feisty dog could probably remove the lid to get inside, it's pretty tight and neither of my dogs has made any attempt. Regarding the programming - the instructions were quite straightforward and I had no problem. It's not intuitive, but that's why they provide instructions. You do have to program it to dispense on the hour (there's no half hour option). I'm not using the recorded voice feature.

Pros:
So convenient!
My dog won't be overweight.

Cons:
It takes about 5 minutes to run enough cycles (1/4 cup at a time) to feed my dog. He eats the quarter cup and waits for it to spit out more.
It might look like there's food in there, but if it's not above the shoot, it won't dispense.

Notes: We're feeding Purina One Smart Blend Lamb & Rice. It holds perhaps 6 days worth of food.

title: Great taste but expensive per mg of Glucosamine HCl compared to other brands
text:
Dog really likes the taste, which is good, although admittedly he's a dog and eats pretty much anything he finds, provided it's old/moldy/has traversed the digestive tract of another animal. So this stuff is a real treat.

However, for me the gold-standard glucosamine supplement is VetriScience GlycoFlex. This "Smarty Paws" has fewer mgs of Glucosamine HCl (500mg per 2 chews, vs. 750mgs for VetriScience), and the price per chew is much higher with Smarty Paws. So, not sure the value is there, especially as our vet recommends the GlycoFlex. Granted, however, that this Smarty Paws is a more general supplement, not just Glucosamine, but I think a good dog food provides many of those other nutrients.

Still, it's a tasty and healthy supplement, and a dog will no doubt appreciate the taste.

Urination has not been in issue until a month ago when he had a slight infection and then had a negative reaction to the antibiotic prescribed. He was still drinking plenty of water, but urination became labored with minimal output, blood, and a strong ammonia scent. I was quite concerned, but didn't want to risk another vet appointment. I started him on Urinary Gold to see if it would help. Within a day his urine output increased and by day 3 everything is back to normal. Lots of beautiful yellow, fresh scented urine. Weird to say I know, but when you love your pet...you jump for joy over healthy bodily functions. Best wishes to everyone.

title: This ball continues to survive my 75 pound Husky!
text:
If you have a highly active and/or aggressive chewer, and like us tend to have the hardest time finding a toy that can withstand your dog's wild ways for longer than 5 minutes, then this is the ball for you!
We have a mutant Husky (we rescued him from a shelter so age and origins are unknown; all we really know is that he is larger than any Husky most have ever laid eyes on- people/vets who lay eyes on him have been overheard referring him with exclamations such as "Wow, he runs like a horse!" "Mommy can we ride him?" and the like...) who loves to chew and destroy the bejesus out of every toy we give him. In our house, most toys last 2-3 minutes before being rendered useless, with lifespans of the "high-performing" "indestructible" toys typically averaging about 5-6 minutes. That is, until my fiancé ordered one of these bad boys. That was almost exactly 2 months ago, and believe it or not this ball is still kicking!
The best part about this ball is that just when you think it's donezo, it literally somehow re-inflates itself and is good as new! I've never seen anything like it! About a week ago, while our mammoth-sized Husky was chomping away on his beloved Chuckit ball, we heard the dreaded sound that signals that a toy's end is near- the inevitable *POP* indicating that "another one bites the dust". We assumed his ball was done for and, like any average unhinged obsessive doggy parents, immediately ordered 3 more with rushed next-day shipping (the dude does love the thing, and it already has lasted longer than ANYTHING else we've tried). However, 5 minutes later he was tossing it around again, and it looked good as new! I am not exaggerating- his original ball is still kicking despite a large and visible gash in the side of it! Even the dog seemed surprised by the ball's continued existence. Our whole family loves this ball so much that we of course did not cancel the 3 more we ordered, so currently there are 4 Chuckits of varying sizes being tossed in, around, and outside of our house at any given moment, and we could not be any happier. title: My beloved dog died and they screwed up her test
text:
We did it for two dogs but only got results for one. I feel like the successful test was actually very accurate. We thought probably something like border collie and Queensland, and sure enough she came back as mostly those breeds and a couple other surprises. Our guess was not just based on her coat and other physicalities, but also her personality and habits (I forget what those traits are called for dogs but anyway she “acts” like her breeds with extremely strong herding instincts and love of livestock!)

I think people unhappy with their results either are guessing solely based on what their dog looks like, or got duped by a shady breeder! If your breeder “guaranteed” certain breeds but you took a test anyway, you must’ve had some doubts…

Anyway, it’s the extreme accuracy that has me so broken hearted that I *could’ve* known what our beloved geriatric lap dog was, but emBark screwed up her test. We sent off the swabs for both dogs, waited patiently, got the results back for our cow dog, then continued to wait for the results of our lap dog. Our geriatric lap dog ended up dying. And THEN we got the notice her swab was ruined just a couple days later. We’re out the money on the test and never get to know her breeds or live vicariously through her closest relatives. If you have a geriatric dog I’d probably skip the test to avoid the very high potential for heartbreak.

title: Watch the videos & follow the instructions
text:
I have found that this device works really well with my dogs. For context, when I purchased this trainer my 3 dogs were already adults...Chocolate Lab (8), Black Lab (7), & German Shepherd (5). When we adopted the black lab 2 years ago (other two were adopted previously) he was an alarm barker and my other two learned to follow his lead.

When using a trainer like this it is important to follow the instructions in order to get good results. If you just start attempting to use it without helping the dogs make a connection to the barking & the sound of the trainer they won't understand & you will be frustrated.

Even with my adult dogs that were set in their ways, it just took a couple of weeks of work to get them on the right track. Now, they don't bark at all if they see me before hearing/seeing something that would've set them off before. They still alarm bark without that preliminary warning, but stop immediately when they hear the trainer. We are still working on getting them to not alarm bark at all, & hoping that will come with some continued work.

title: RIDICULOUS
text:
I BOUGHT A BARK COLLAR 7 YEARS AGO FROM THIS COMPANY WHEN MY BABY WAS A PUPPY. IT WAS AND IS WORTH ITS WEIGHT IN GOLD SO I IGNORED THE BAD REVIEWS. MY BAD.

THE BARK COLLAR IS REFILLED WITH A CANISTER OF CITRONELLA WHICH IS INEXPENSIVE. I ONLY HAD TO PUT IT ON HIM 3-4 TIMES. HE HATED IT SO MUCH, AFTER THAT, I ONLY HAD TO HOLD IT UP FOR HIM TO SEE AND HE TOOK OFF FOR THE NEAREST SAFE HAVEN; UNDER A TABLE, BED, WHATNOT.

HERE'S WHY IT'S STILL WORTH ITS WEIGHT IN GOLD. I HAVE A LITTLE 19 LB PEKAPOO (PEKINGESE AND POODLE). ANYONE WHO OWNS A SMALL DOG KNOWS (OR SHOULD) THAT IF THEY GET HOLD OF A BONE IT'S A DISASTER. 1 - YOU AREN'T GOING TO GET IT AWAY FROM THEM WITHOUT HURTING THEM IN SOME WAY (DON'T HAVE THE HEART FOR THAT) AND 2- IF YOU DON'T GET IT AWAY FROM THEM THERE'S A DEFINITE CHANCE IT COULD KILL THEM.

MY LITTLE GUY GOT A NASTY RAGGED BONE THAT WAS FORTUNATELY LONG ENOUGH FOR ME TO GRAB ONE END OF IT. I YELLED, I SWEET TALKED, I PRETENDED TO CRY. NO LUCK. SO I THOUGHT, OK, I'LL KEEP HOLD OF THE BONE WITH ONE HAND AND PICK HIM UP, CARRY HIM HOME AND FIGURE SOMETHING OUT. IN ORDER TO DO THAT, I HAD TO PUT THE LEASH HANDLE IN MY COAST POCKET TO FREE UP A HAND.. BUT THE BARK COLLAR WAS IN MY POCKET. SO I TOOK IT OUT AND WHEN HE SAW IT, HE DROPPED THE BONE!!!!!!!!!!!!

BACK TO THE BUSINESS AT HAND. THIS DEVICE IS COMPLICATED; YOU HAVE TO MEMORIZE HOW TO USE THE DIFFERENT FUNCTIONS (EITHER THAT OR CARRY CRIB NOTES AROUND). THE VIBRATING AND BEEPING FEATURES ARE COMPLETELY USELESS. I CAN BARELY FEEL THE VIBRATION AND BARELY HEAR THE BEEPING. NO DOG THAT IS GOING AFTER SOMETHING IS GOING TO PAY ANY ATTENTION. ESPECIALLY BECAUSE I'M PRETTY SURE HE CAN'T FEEL OR HEAR IT. SO THAT LEAVES THE CITRONELLA SPRAY FEATURE. NOT NEARLY AS STRONG AS THE BARK COLLAR. HE NEVER FLINCHED WHEN I ACTIVATED IT. I'S SOMEWHAT HEAVY SO IT MOVES A LITTLE WHEN HE RUNS SO IT MUST HAVE MISSED HIM BECAUSE AS WE KNOW FROM THE ABOVE STORY - WE KNOW HOW MUCH HE HATES THAT CITRONELLA!

IT'S NOT A RETURNABLE ITEM SO I JUST CONTACTED AMAZON DIRECTLY AND VOILA, THREW IT AWAY AND GOT MY MONEY BACK.

I READ THE VENDOR'S RESPONSES TO THE NEGATIVE COMMENTS AND I REALLY APPRECIATE IT WHEN A COMPANY TRIES TO MAKE THINGS RIGHT WHICH WAS ANOTHER REASON I TOOK A CHANCE. BUT I DON'T HAVE THE TIME NOR THE PATIENCE FOR DIFFICULT TO DEAL WITH PRODUCTS ESPECIALLY WHEN THEY DON'T WORK. SOMEBODY NEEDS TO GO BACK TO THE DRAWING BOARD.

title: This is an ingenious product!
text:
I actually have the Catgenie 60 and I absolutely love it. It saves me so much time digging through cat poop on a daily basis. It remains clean and odorless for the 2 years it has been in use.

Here are a few negatives you should consider (note that the 120 model may have already fixed these issues)
The bowl warps due to the heat from the blow dryer overtime and stops spinning due to the bowl hitting against a gear. I fixed this by simply adding a washer under the bowl. Additionally, every 4-5 months, the water sensor gets dirty and water will not enter the bowl anymore. The fix would be to manually remove the sensor and clean it off.

Although the machine is not perfect, I still give it a 5 stars because it saved me so much time and allows me to go on short vacations away from home.

Spends much of the day/evening inside napping on it. We live in Northern California so do not have extreme winters. The bed is inside a portable greenhouse that is being used as a feral cat “house”. So can stay nice and dry during rainy days. On the occasion it does get slightly damp (from the cat’s wet fur), I fluff it in my dryer for a few mins. My only slight critique is about the sides of the bed. They are not super sturdy. IE, when my heavy boy leans his lead on them, the sides tend to sink down a bit versus staying up. He does not seem to mind since again love this, but thought to mention. Overall thrilled with this product and will buy again.
